     {q:"Weathering is best described as the process that ___.", options:["A concept unrelated to physical geography","Instantly transforms rock into soil with no gradual process","Breaks down rock into smaller pieces through physical or chemical processes","Transports weathered material from one location to another"], answer:2},
     {q:"A city’s site refers to ___.", options:["The total population living within the city","Its exact physical location and local features","Its position relative to surrounding regions","A concept unrelated to urban geography"], answer:1},
     {q:"The Great Lakes are best described as ___.", options:["A chain of saltwater lakes found only in Canada","The largest group of freshwater lakes in the world","A single small lake located entirely within Ontario","A concept unrelated to physical geography"], answer:1},
     {q:"Housing affordability refers to the relationship between ___.", options:["Housing costs and household income","The physical size of a home and its location only","A concept unrelated to urban geography","The number of homes built in a single year"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why is it useful to review physical and urban geography topics like weathering, site and situation, the Great Lakes, and housing affordability together?", options:["It reinforces how physical processes and human settlement patterns both shape the geography of a region","Each topic must be studied with no connection to the others","Review is never useful in social studies","These topics have no meaningful connections"], answer:0}
